verbs.description: unsharpen (third-person singular simple present unsharpens, present participle unsharpening, simple past and past participle unsharpened)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To render unsharp; to spoil the sharpness of (something).
(transitive, computer graphics) To undo a sharpening operation on (an image).
examples: When it sharpens the image, you can't unsharpen it again without losing data.
